### Current Progress

- **Phase 1: Align with current Skaia page model** — ✅ Complete
  - `models.Page` with `Content` JSONB all set
  - `models.PageSection` covers typed sections with `section_type` field
  - Page CRUD endpoints at `/pages/*` exist
  
- **Phase 2: Add explicit section metadata** — ✅ Complete
  - ✅ Frontend: 14 section types defined in `types.ts` (hero, card_group, data_sources, derived_section, custom_section, etc.)
  - ✅ Frontend: `BLOCK_MAP` in `BlockRenderer.tsx` maps all section types to components
  - ✅ Frontend: `SECTION_TYPE_GROUPS` for organized UI picker (featured, content, integration)
  - ✅ Backend: `/config/sections` and `/config/section-types/{type}` registry endpoints added via `backend/internal/s_registry`
  - ✅ Backend: Page saves reject invalid content JSON, missing/unknown `section_type`, and malformed section config

- **Phase 3: Enforce integration primitives** — ✅ Complete
  - ✅ Frontend: `DataSourcesBlock`, `DerivedSectionBlock`, `CustomSectionBlock` components implemented
  - ✅ Frontend: Builder can create and edit all integration block types
  - ✅ Backend: Positive `derived_section.config.datasource_id` and `custom_section.config.custom_section_id` refs are validated on page create/update; empty draft refs remain allowed

- **Phase 4: Add component registry and bind-point contracts** — ⬜ Not started
  - Need canonical component metadata for primitive and compound components.
  - Need bind-point contracts for text, rich text, number, boolean, media, link/action, object, array, and generic values.
  - Need style target metadata and constrained style override validation.
  - Need custom HTML/component inspection strategy that generates explicit saved metadata instead of relying on runtime DOM guessing.

- **Phase 5: Open derived/custom sections to registered primitive components** — ⬜ Not started
  - `derived_section` should let the builder pick the repeated row component through a component registry.
  - `custom_section` should support saved custom components/templates with documented bind points and validation.
  - Datasource columns/object paths/literals should map into component bind points per row.
  - Row rendering should support cards, text, buttons, checkboxes, media, links, icons/badges, div/container primitives, and compound layouts.

- **Phase 6: Convert routes to dynamic page rendering** — ⬜ Not started
- **Phase 7: Add versioning and migration** — ⬜ Not started

### Backend Registry & Validation (2026-05-29)

✅ **Section registry and endpoints added:**
- `backend/internal/s_registry` owns the canonical 14 supported section definitions
- `GET /config/sections` lists section definitions and config schemas
- `GET /config/section-types/{type}` returns one section definition or 404

✅ **Page save validation added:**
- `POST /pages` and `PUT /pages/{id}` now validate page `Content` before persistence
- Unknown/missing `section_type` returns 400 via `page.ErrInvalidContent`
- Invalid datasource/custom-section IDs in integration blocks return 400
- Validation accepts both stringified config JSON and object config JSON

✅ **Verification recorded by current changes:**
- `JWT_SECRET=test-secret go test ./internal/s_registry ./internal/page ./internal/config`
- Full `JWT_SECRET=test-secret go test ./...` still needs to be rerun after the active worktree changes are finalized.

### Component Registry Expansion (2026-05-29)

🟡 **Requirements now captured in the plan:**
- The builder must allow clients to choose a registered component for repeated datasource rows in `derived_section` and `custom_section`.
- Supported selectable components should include primitive elements (`div`, text, button, checkbox, image/video/media, link, icon/badge) and compound repeatable components such as cards or card-with-media/text/action layouts.
- Each component definition must document bind points, accepted data kinds, required/fallback behavior, style targets, slot/child rules, and validation rules.
- Complex data must be bindable through object paths and typed bind points, not only flat string columns.
- Custom HTML/component input may use detection to propose bind points, but saved custom components should persist explicit generated metadata for stable validation/rendering.
- Backend validation remains authoritative for component type, bind-point keys, datasource column/value compatibility, required bindings, and style override safety.

🟡 **Preferred architecture:**
- Metadata-first for first-party primitive and compound components.
- Inspector-assisted metadata generation for custom HTML/custom components.
- Runtime renderer applies `component_type`, `bindings`, `row_key_column`, `row_overrides`, and `style_overrides` to each datasource row.

### Frontend CSS & Component Consolidation (2026-05-29)

✅ **Shared primitives added to `index.css`:**
- `.btn-*` variants: primary, secondary, ghost, danger, warning + sizing (sm, lg, block)
- `.badge-*` variants: secondary, success, warning, error, info
- `.page-*` surface layout: shell, header, header__main, header__actions, title, subtitle
- `.ui-*` tooling: panel, toolbar, actions, actions--center, actions--end, tabs, tab, tab--active, empty, dialog*
- `.form-*` primitives: grid, actions, check
- `.card` system: base, interactive, outlined, flat, compact, section, forum, store, highlight
- `.section` system: block, header, content

✅ **Form inputs standardized in `FormGroup.css`:**
- Checkbox sizing reset to `1rem × 1rem` with `padding: 0`
- Input/textarea focus state with `--primary-color` ring
- Disabled state styling

⚠️ **Ongoing migration:**
- ErrorPage buttons, store empty state moved to primitives
- High-drift components identified but not yet modularized: need continued migration as pages are touched

